com.yworks.yfiles.graphml

Class TypedKeyMapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yworks.yfiles.graphml.TypedKeyMapper

  • public final class TypedKeyMapper
extends Object
    A specialized IMapper-like implementation that uses TypedKeys as the keys and their corresponding strongly typed values as the values.

      • get

        public final <T> T get(TypedKey<T> key)
        Finds the associated value for the given key in the mapping or (re-)associates the given key with the value provided, removing previous associations.

        In order to remove an association the removeValue(TypedKey) method should be preferred over calling this method using a default value.

        Parameters:
        key - The key to use as the index.
        See Also:
        removeValue(TypedKey)

      • removeValue

        public final <T> void removeValue(TypedKey<T> key)
        Removes a previously created association with the given key.
        Parameters:
        key - The key to remove from the mapping.

      • set

        public final <T> void set(TypedKey<T> key,

        Previous values are overwritten.

        Type Parameters:

        Parameters:
        key - The key.
        value - The value.
